        <headline>Heat Advisory issued August 7 at 9:02PM CDT until August 8 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Air temperatures and heat index values up to 106.

* WHERE...In Kansas, Decatur, Graham, Norton, Sheridan, and Gove
Counties. In Nebraska, Red Willow County.

* WHEN...From 1 PM to 8 PM CDT Friday.

* IMPACTS...Heat related illnesses increase significantly during
extreme heat events.
</description>
        <instruction>Take extra precautions when outside. Wear lightweight and loose
fitting clothing. Try to limit strenuous activities to early morning
or evening. Take action when you see symptoms of heat exhaustion and
heat stroke.

Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
